Statistical mechanics of DNA-bound particles

Here we outline the exact theory for T molecular species simultaneously interacting with one-dimensional DNA (details and extensions are provided in SI Appendix). The DNA-bound particles are subject to steric exclusion and may also be partially unwrapped. Let us (k, l) (s  {1, 2, . . . , T }) denote the binding energy of a particle of type s attached to bps k, . . . , l. One can show that the

