1.4

Sequence-specific nucleosome formation energies

The simplest sequence-dependent model of nucleosome formation assumes that the nucleosome energy depends only on the mono- and dinucleotide counts in the nucleosomal site [54]. Thus for the sequence S1 S2 . . . SN , the nucleosome N N -1 formation energy is Si Si+1 , where Si and Si Si+1 are the i=1 Si + i=1 mono- and dinucleotide contributions, respectively. Here we consider a symmetrized version of the model, with A = T , C = G and 10 unique dinucleotide energies: AA/T T , AC/GT , AG/CT , AT , CA/T G , CC/GG , CG , GA/T C , GC , T A . Using Eq. (S14), we can estimate all 12 's for a model in which nucleosomes are the only particle type and unwrapping is allowed. For each sequence starting a bp i and ending at bp j , we have
