Figure S4: Sensitivity of the predicted inter-dyad distribution to model parameters describing higher-order chromatin structure. The unwrapping potential is based on nucleosome crystal structures (SI Results, Model A). (A) Root-mean-square error (RMS) of the predicted inter-dyad distribution, as a function of the position and the depth of the first minimum outside of the nucleosome core (Fig. 1B). The depth of the first minimum is computed with respect to uhalf (x = 73 bp). (B) The linear correlation coefficient between oscillations in the predicted and observed inter-dyad distributions (rosc ), as a function of the position and the depth of the first minimum outside of the nucleosome core (Fig. 1B). The oscillations were obtained by subtracting the smooth background from inter-dyad distributions, as described in the Fig. 1 caption. In both panels, model parameters that were not varied were kept fixed at their best-fit values (SI Results, Model A).

